---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ThisDayInHistory from '../components/ThisDayInHistory.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="This Day in History — What Happened Today? | Clockr"
	description="Discover notable events, births, and deaths that happened on this day throughout history. Browse any date using Wikipedia's On This Day data."
	category="history"
>
	<div class="tdih-page">
		<div class="tdih-header">
			<div class="tdih-eyebrow">
				<span class="tdih-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				HISTORY
			</div>
			<h1 class="tdih-title">
				<span class="tdih-gradient">This Day in History</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="tdih-subtitle">
				Discover what happened on this day throughout history
			</p>
		</div>

		<ThisDayInHistory client:load />

		<section class="tdih-how">
			<h2 class="tdih-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="tdih-how-card">
				<p>
					This tool pulls its data from Wikipedia&apos;s open &ldquo;On This
					Day&rdquo; REST API — a free, community-maintained feed that lists
					notable events, births, and deaths associated with each calendar date.
					Thousands of volunteer editors curate and verify the entries over time,
					so the content grows and improves as Wikipedia itself does. Clockr
					fetches the feed for your chosen month and day directly in your
					browser; no account or API key is required.
				</p>
				<p>
					History does not happen on a single timeline for each date on the
					calendar. When you look at 26 June, you might see a battle from the
					15th century alongside a scientific breakthrough from the 20th and a
					political event from last decade. The same month-and-day recurs every
					year, so each date accumulates moments from across centuries and
					continents — which is why the results are grouped by year rather than
					presented as one continuous story.
				</p>
				<p>
					Wikipedia&apos;s coverage reflects what has been documented and deemed
					notable by its editors, which means some cultures, regions, and time
					periods are represented more fully than others. The lists favour
					well-sourced, widely recognised events rather than attempting to be a
					complete archive of everything that ever occurred on a given day. Use
					this page as a starting point for curiosity — and follow the
					&ldquo;Read more&rdquo; links to explore any entry in depth on
					Wikipedia.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="tdih-faq">
			<h2 class="tdih-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="tdih-faq-list">
				<details class="tdih-faq-item">
					<summary class="tdih-faq-question"
						>What happened on this day in history?</summary
					>
					<div class="tdih-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Open this page to see a curated selection of events, births, and
							deaths tied to today&apos;s calendar date. Switch between the
							Events, Births, and Deaths tabs to explore each category. Use the
							arrow buttons or date picker to browse any other day of the year.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="tdih-faq-item">
					<summary class="tdih-faq-question">How is this data sourced?</summary>
					<div class="tdih-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Data comes from the English Wikipedia &ldquo;On This Day&rdquo; API
							(<code>en.wikipedia.org/api/rest_v1/feed/onthisday</code>). Entries
							are written and maintained by Wikipedia volunteers and updated as
							articles change. Clockr requests the feed for your selected month
							and day and displays a filtered list of the most notable items with
							links back to Wikipedia.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="tdih-faq-item">
					<summary class="tdih-faq-question"
						>Can I look up any date in history?</summary
					>
					<div class="tdih-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Yes. Use the left and right arrows to step through consecutive
							days, or enter any date in the date field to jump directly to that
							month and day. The tool uses the calendar month and day only — the
							year you type is ignored for the lookup, because historical
							entries are tied to recurring dates like &ldquo;26 June&rdquo;
							rather than a specific year.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="tdih-faq-item">
					<summary class="tdih-faq-question"
						>Why are some years better represented than others?</summary
					>
					<div class="tdih-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Wikipedia&apos;s coverage depends on which topics have articles and
							which events editors have added to the On This Day lists. Recent
							decades, major world powers, and widely documented fields such as
							science and sport tend to have more entries. Older, local, or
							less-documented events may appear less often — this is a limitation
							of the source material, not the calculator.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="tdih-faq-item">
					<summary class="tdih-faq-question"
						>How do I find out who was born on my birthday?</summary
					>
					<div class="tdih-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Enter your birthday in the date field (any year works), then open
							the Births tab. You&apos;ll see notable people born on that
							month-and-day, with a short description and a Wikipedia link for
							each entry.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="tdih-faq-item">
					<summary class="tdih-faq-question"
						>Can I share today&apos;s history with someone?</summary
					>
					<div class="tdih-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Copy the URL from your browser&apos;s address bar and send it to
							friends or family. When they open the link on the same calendar
							date, they&apos;ll see that day&apos;s history. To share a
							different date, navigate to it first so they see the same results
							when they visit.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="tdih-related">
			<h3 class="tdih-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="tdih-related-grid">
				<a href="/day-of-week" class="tdih-related-card"
					><span class="tdih-related-name">Day of the Week Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/year-progress" class="tdih-related-card"
					><span class="tdih-related-name">Year Progress Bar</span></a
				>
				<a href="/days-until-christmas" class="tdih-related-card"
					><span class="tdih-related-name">Days Until Christmas</span></a
				>
				<a href="/anniversary-calculator" class="tdih-related-card"
					><span class="tdih-related-name">Anniversary Calculator</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.tdih-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.tdih-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.tdih-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d97706, #f59e0b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.tdih-eyebrow-square {
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 2px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d97706, #f59e0b);
		flex-shrink: 0;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: initial;
	}

	.tdih-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.tdih-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d97706, #f59e0b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.tdih-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.tdih-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.tdih-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.tdih-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.tdih-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.tdih-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.tdih-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.tdih-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.tdih-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.tdih-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d97706, #f59e0b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.tdih-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.tdih-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d97706, #f59e0b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.tdih-faq-item[open] .tdih-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.tdih-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.tdih-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.tdih-faq-answer code {
		font-size: 12px;
		color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.85);
		word-break: break-all;
	}

	.tdih-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.tdih-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.tdih-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.tdih-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.tdih-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.4);
	}

	.tdih-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d97706, #f59e0b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	/* This Day in History tool */
	.tdih-tool {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.tdih-date-nav {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 24px;
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	.tdih-nav-btn {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		width: 44px;
		height: 44px;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.25);
		border-radius: 12px;
		cursor: pointer;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #f59e0b;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease;
	}

	.tdih-nav-btn:hover {
		border-color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.5);
		background: rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.08);
	}

	.tdih-date-display {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(28px, 5vw, 40px);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d97706, #f59e0b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		min-width: 160px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.tdih-date-input-wrap {
		max-width: 320px;
		margin: 0 auto 28px;
	}

	.tdih-tabs {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 10px;
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	.tdih-tab {
		padding: 14px 12px;
		background: rgba(12, 12, 12, 0.6);
		border: 1px solid rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.25);
		border-radius: 12px;
		cursor: pointer;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease,
			box-shadow 0.2s ease;
	}

	.tdih-tab:hover {
		border-color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.5);
		background: rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.08);
	}

	.tdih-tab--active {
		border-color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.7);
		background: rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.15);
		box-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.2);
		color: #fff;
		background-image: linear-gradient(135deg, #d97706, #f59e0b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.tdih-loading {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 16px;
		padding: 24px 0;
	}

	.tdih-spinner {
		width: 36px;
		height: 36px;
		border: 3px solid rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.2);
		border-top-color: #f59e0b;
		border-radius: 50%;
		animation: tdih-spin 0.8s linear infinite;
	}

	@keyframes tdih-spin {
		to {
			transform: rotate(360deg);
		}
	}

	.tdih-loading-text {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.tdih-skeleton-list {
		width: 100%;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 12px;
		margin-top: 8px;
	}

	.tdih-skeleton-card {
		height: 88px;
		background: linear-gradient(
			90deg,
			rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.06) 0%,
			rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.12) 50%,
			rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.06) 100%
		);
		background-size: 200% 100%;
		border-radius: 12px;
		animation: tdih-shimmer 1.4s ease-in-out infinite;
	}

	@keyframes tdih-shimmer {
		0% {
			background-position: 200% 0;
		}
		100% {
			background-position: -200% 0;
		}
	}

	.tdih-error {
		text-align: center;
		padding: 32px 24px;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.2);
		border-radius: 14px;
	}

	.tdih-error p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.tdih-retry-btn {
		padding: 12px 24px;
		background: rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.15);
		border: 1px solid rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.4);
		border-radius: 10px;
		cursor: pointer;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #f59e0b;
		transition: background 0.2s ease;
	}

	.tdih-retry-btn:hover {
		background: rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.25);
	}

	.tdih-empty {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		text-align: center;
		padding: 32px 16px;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.tdih-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.tdih-item {
		display: flex;
		gap: 20px;
		align-items: flex-start;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-left: 3px solid #d97706;
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px;
	}

	.tdih-item-year {
		flex-shrink: 0;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(22px, 4vw, 28px);
		font-weight: 900;
		line-height: 1.1;
		min-width: 64px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d97706, #f59e0b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.tdih-item-body {
		flex: 1;
		min-width: 0;
	}

	.tdih-item-text {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
		line-height: 1.65;
		margin: 0 0 10px;
	}

	.tdih-read-more {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #f59e0b;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.tdih-read-more:hover {
		color: #fbbf24;
		text-decoration: underline;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.tdih-title {
			font-size: 44px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		.tdih-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.tdih-item {
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 8px;
		}

		.tdih-item-year {
			min-width: 0;
		}
	}
</style>
